cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.CL 

This paper is about predicting future semantic segmentation from RGB frames using a temporal encoder-decoder network architecture. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new knowledge distillation training framework, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with decision-making in robotics and autonomous driving systems, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.RO (Robotics). Finally, the paper involves natural language processing techniques to describe the problem and the proposed method, which could fall under cs.CL (Computation and Language).
